Victim Support are providing free drop-in services for those who have been affected by the investigation into Legacy Independent Funeral Directors.
These session aim to support those who are suffering with their mental or physical health as a result of the discoveries around Legacy Funeral Directors, are worried about the investigation, or just feel they want to talk to someone. These sessions are free and the advice given is confidential.
The drop-in session are taking place-
Wednesday 2nd October 2024 10am to 1pm
@Spring Bank Community Centre
Tuesday 8th October 2024 1pm to 4pm
@East Riding Leisure Centre Haltemprice
Thursday 17th October 2024 1pm to 4pm
@Lonsdale Community Centre
Wednesday 23rd October 2024 10am to 1pm
@Brough Community Centre
If you are unable to attend any of the above sessions, you can call Victim Support on 0808 28 111 36 to speak to an advisor.
I would encourage anyone affected to pop along, even if it’s just for a chat and a cuppa!
